{"questionId":"13806216","questionHtml":"<p>Find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;in terms of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1 (chain rule)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for correct first term&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>,&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em> for attempt to use the chain rule, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for correct use of chain rule&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>×</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.&nbsp;Award at most <em><strong>A1M1A0</strong> </em>if additional terms are seen. The answer is not required to be simplified beyond what is shown in the markscheme.</p>\n<p><strong><br>METHOD 2 (quotient rule)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>007</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>007</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>007</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>007</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong> </em>for attempt to use quotient rule, <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for correct use.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>007</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>007</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>007</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>150</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for correct numerator and <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for correct denominator.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13806216","referenceCode":"23N.2.AHL.TZ0.4c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find h'x in terms of x.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.9—Differentiating standard functions and derivative rules","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}